<TITLE> Corruption, tax evasion charges framed against Tuku </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Sunday framed charges in a corruption case against former BNP minister Iqbal Hasan Mahmud Tuku and his family. The court also framed charges in a tax evasion case against Tuku the same day. Judge Md Ashraf Hossain of the special judge's court-5 will hear witness testimonies Monday in the case filed by the Anticorruption Commission. ACC deputy director Shahriar Chowdhury filed a complaint with Mohammadpur Police Station on June 28 against Tuku and his family for concealing the sources of assets worth Tk 4.96 crore. The same court set Thursday to hear witnesses in the tax evasion case filed by the National Board of Revenue. The former minister faces allegations of tax evasion during the years 1999 to 2007. Joint forces arrested Tuku on Feb 3. Police arrested his wife Romana Mahmud and their daughter Sara Hasin Mahmud on July 3. Tuku's son Abed Hasan Mahmud turned himself in to the Metropolitan Senior Special Judge's Court the same day. The cases were later transferred to the special judge's court set up in the Jatiya Sangsad premises. bdnews24.c
